Add Preconnect to DSE with privacy mode enabled

Currently, the SearchEnginePreconnector creates a preconnect to the
search engine with privacy mode disabled, as that is thought to be most
likely to be used when making search requests. However, some search
requests may use connections with privacy mode enabled instead as a
result of cookie deprecation, etc., so this CL adds a feature to add
a preconnect to the search engine with privacy mode enabled as well.

https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/3465784
previously removed this preconnect as it was thought to be not useful,
but it may be useful now.

[FspCache] Initialize via the CacheManager using ProvidedFileSystemInfo

Previously CacheManager::InitializeForProvider() and
CacheManager::UninitializeForProvider() would take in the provider
folder name. However, extracting the provider folder name from the
ProvidedFileSystemInfo required some processing. This was okay when
the CacheManager::InitializeForProvider() was called from one place
(the CloudFileSystem). But now the complementary
CacheManager::UninitializeForProvider() will be called in a different
place in the follow up CL:5417754.

It is better not to rely on the callers to properly extract out the
provider folder name, instead the CacheManager should handle this logic.

Update CacheManager::InitializeForProvider() and
CacheManager::UninitializeForProvider() to accept a
ProvidedFileSystemInfo.

Define the == operator for the ProvidedFileSystemInfo so that it can be
compared in the FileSystemProviderCloudFileSystemTest.

Test: unit_tests --gtest_filter=FileSystemProviderCloudFileSystemTest*
Test: unit_tests --gtest_filter=FileSystemProviderCacheManagerImplTest*

[Telemetry] Add interfaces for interactive routines

Add a field `interaction` to the waiting state so that a routine can
ask callers to react to an interaction request. For interactions that
need to be replied to, callers should invoke the `ReplyToInquiry`
method.

The underlying implementation of `ReplyInquiry` in cros_healthd was
introduced in CL:5171546.

The interaction field and `ReplyToInquiry` method will be exposed to the
telemetry extension in CL:5411712.

launcher: add UMA metrics for image search.

This CL adds several image search metrics.
1. As part of PnP request, we add a UMA to track the user image indexing
distribution and the indexing success rate.
2. We add more re-tries and add another metric to check when is the ICA
DLC available. The ICA initialization fail rate is high, and it is
suspicious that it is not ready until all re-tries have been attempted.
